    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1871-10-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1871-10-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="88" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d88">
                <head>No. 88.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hurlbut</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                        the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Bogota</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1871-10-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 7, 1871</date>.
                                (Received October 30.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 63.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I am just informed by the secretary of
                            foreign relations that the commandant of the port of Colon (Aspinwall)
                            required bonds from the captain and agents of the American steamer
                            Virginius, not to leave that port, which order the President had
                            immediately disavowed and annulled.</p>
                <p>I expressed at once the thanks of the United States for the
                            promptness-with which this had been done, without any solicitation on
                            our part, for I had no knowledge of the matter in any form. For some
                            reason I have received no communication on the subject from Consul
                            Perry. It is probably on the way and will arrive by next mail.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>S. A. HURLBUT,</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
